sice 2.2.0:
new commands for 'tuya-smart-device' node:

 CONNECTION operations (_standby)

 In tuyadDAEMON is implemented as a pseudoDP:  see "pseudo DPs" node.
 The pseudoDP are handled as standard native device DPS, but a node acts as adapter before post it to a device.
 Valid for all real devices using tuya-smart-devices node.
````
  tuyaDAEMON extrension:  (only SET)
     {
      "toDev":"60a823fffe****",     // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
      "payload": {
          "devId": "60a453fffe*****",   // cid, only for virtual devices (string)   
          "dps":"_standby",                                           // pseudoDP    
          "set": true|false|"ON"|"OFF"                         // BOOLEAN, STRING   
          } }

    native: [see here](https://github.com/vinodsr/node-red-contrib-tuya-smart-device)
     {
     "toDev":"60a823fffe****",      // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
     "payload": {
          "operation": "CONTROL",       
          "action": "CONNECT"                    // or "DISCONNECT"|"RECONNECTS"
          }}
````          
 TIMEOUT operations (_findTimeout & _retyTimeout)   

 In tuyadDAEMON implemented as two pseudoDP: _findTimeout & _retyTimeout. See "pseudo DPs" node. 
 Also used in the implementation of "dynamic rety" node.
 Valid for all real devices using tuya-smart-devices node.
````
 tuyaDAEMON extrension:   (only SET)
     {
      "toDev":"60a823fffe****",     // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
      "payload": {
          "devId": "60a453fffe*****",   // cid, only for virtual devices (string)   
          "dps":"_findTimeout"|"_retyTimeout",                      // pseudoDP    
          "set": 2000                                            // timeout in ms   
          } }


  native: [see here](https://github.com/vinodsr/node-red-contrib-tuya-smart-device)
      {
      "to":"60a823fff******",      // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID/gatewayID
      "payload": {
         "operation": "CONTROL",       
         "action": "SET_RETY_TIMEOUT"                 // or  "SET_FIND_TIMEOUT"
         "value": number                                      // timeout in ms
          }}
````

 new operation for tuya devices:
 [see](https://codetheweb.github.io/tuyapi/index.html#tuyadevice)

 REFRESH operation _refresh & _refreshCycle 

  In tuyadDAEMON implemented as two  pseudoDP: _refresh & _refreshCycle  see "REFRESH" subflow. 

  Valid for a few real devices that use the tuya-smart-device node and implement REFRESH.
 note: usable only with devices that have a REFRESH node in the CORE flow and the 'REFRESH' capability in global.alldevices. 
 Consider it an optional feature: it can be added at a later time.
````
 tuyaDAEMON extrension:  (only SET)
     {
      "toDev":"60a823fffe****",      // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
      "payload": {
          "devId": "60a453fffe*****",   // cid, only for virtual devices (string)   
          "dps":"_refresh",                        // pseudoDP: immediare command    
          "set": any            // required but not used: the SET acts as trigger  
          } }

tuyaDAEMON extrension:  (only SET)
     {
      "toDev":"60a823fffe****",     // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
      "payload": {
          "devId": "60a453fffe*****",   // cid, only for virtual devices (string)   
          "dps":_refreshCycle",                                       // pseudoDP    
          "set": NUM(rate)| false|"OFF"                    // ON (rate in s)| OFF   
          } }


native: [see here](https://codetheweb.github.io/tuyapi/index.html#tuyadevice)
      {
      "toDev":"60a823fffe****",     // tuyaDAEMON extrension: deviceID|gatewayID
      "payload": { 
         "devId": "60a453fffe*****",   // cid, only for virtual devices (string)   
         "operation": "REFRESH",           // usually used alone or with one of:
           "dps": undefined|dp,                             //refreshs only a dp
           "requestedDPS":[1,9,6,17,18,19,20],               // refresh a dp set
           "schema":true                                      // refresh all dps
          }}
````

